The paper discusses feature selection algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a genetic programming approach, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of synthetic bad features and the creation of benchmark datasets suggest the sub-category of cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the paper discusses the difficulty of automatically generating complex, redundant features, which is a problem in software engineering, suggesting the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
